org.hps.monitoring.ecal.eventdisplay.util

Class CrystalDataSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hps.monitoring.ecal.eventdisplay.util.CrystalDataSet

  • public class CrystalDataSet
extends Object
    Class CrystalDataSet contains all of the hardware data for a single calorimeter crystal as defined in the crystal hardware reference sheet.

    • Nested Class Summary

      static class  CrystalDataSet.Motherboard

      Class Preamplifier represents the number of a crystal's preamplifier.

    • Constructor Detail

      • CrystalDataSet

        public CrystalDataSet(int ix,
                      int iy,
                      int apd,
                      String preamp,
                      int ledChannel,
                      double ledDriver,
                      int fadcSlot,
                      int fadcChannel,
                      int splitter,
                      int hvGroup,
                      int jout,
                      String mb,
                      int channel,
                      int gain)
        Defines the data set.
        Parameters:
        ix - - The crystal's x-index in the LCSimcoordinate system.
        iy - - The crystal's y-index in the LCSimcoordinate system.
        apd - - The number of the APD attached to the crystal.
        preamp - - The number of the crystal's preamplifier. This may also include a reference wire color.
        ledChannel - - The channel number for the crystal's LED.
        ledDriver -
        fadcSlot - - The FADC slot the crystal occupies.
        fadcChannel - - The channel number through which the crystal communicates with the FADC.
        splitter - - The number of the crystal's splitter.
        hvGroup - - The high voltage group for which the crystal is a member.
        jout - - The crystal's signal channel group.
        mb - - The position of the motherboard associated with the crystal.
        channel - - The channel associated with the crystal.
        gain - - The crystal's gain.
